text: right Aija Barča (born 26 October 1949www.cvk.lv) is a Latvian pedagogue and politician and a Deputy of the Saeima in 1998-2002 and since 2006. She was elected from the social democratic list in the 7th Saeima, from People's Party in the 9th and from the Union of Greens and Farmers in the 10th and 11th. ==References== Category:1949 births Category:Living people Category:People from Ventspils Municipality Category:Latvian Green Party politicians Category:Latvian Social Democratic Workers' Party politicians Category:People's Party (Latvia) politicians Category:Liepāja Party politicians Category:Deputies of the 7th Saeima Category:Deputies of the 9th Saeima Category:Deputies of the 10th Saeima Category:Deputies of the 11th Saeima Category:Deputies of the 12th Saeima Category:Women deputies of the Saeima Category:University of Liepāja alumni Category:21st-century Latvian women politicians Category:20th-century Latvian women politicians
